Mohun Bagan champions of India 1997/98.

[JCT Mills is an abbreviation for Jagatjit Cotton Textile Mills]

Promoted: Tollygunge Agragami (Calcutta) and ITI (Bangalore).
Relegated: no teams were relegated.


Second Division
---------------

Preliminary Stage (in 3 groups of 6 teams; all played 5 matches).

Group A (Jabalpur): qualified: 1.Kerala Police (Tiruvananthapuram)
        and 2.Tollygunge Agragami (Calcutta); other teams now known.

Group B (Guwahati): 1.Border Security Force (Jalandhar) and 2.Mohammedan
        Sporting (Calcutta); other teams: Tisco (Bihar), TBL FC (Mizoram),
        City Club (Delhi) and Assam Special Reserve Force (Guwahati).

Group C (Bangalore): qualified: 1.ITI (Bangalore) 5 4 1 0 13 and 2.Sesa
        Sports Club (Goa) 5 3 2 0 11; other teams: 3.State Bank of Travancore 
        (Kerala), 4.Central Railway (Mumbia), 5.South Central Railway
        (Secundarabad), 6.Southern Railway (Chennai).

Final Stage (Bangalore)

Table:

 1.Tollygunge Agragami 5                    [Calcutta]   Promoted
 2.ITI                 5                    [Bangalore]  Promoted
 3.Sesa SC             5                    [Goa]
 4.Border SF           5  1  2  2  5- 6  5  [Jalandhar]
 5.Mohammedan Sporting 5                    [Calcutta]
 6.Kerala Police       5  0  2  3        2  [Tiruvananthapuram]

