Cup Tournaments 1997/98
=======================

20th Federation Cup 1997 (in Calcutta, Guwahati and Bangalore)

[Official name: Kalyani Black Label Federation Cup.]

[No data on regional qualifiers.  Qualified from northern
 section: Punjab Police; from eastern section: Mizo Islanders,
 Mohammedan Sporting, Eastern Railway; from southern section:
 Integral Coach Factory, State Bank Travancore; western section:
 Marmagao Port Trust, Churchill Brothers.  India's first professional
 club, FC Kochin, were refused participation as the AIFF was against
 participation of a club not having played in a local league before.]

